sequenceDiagram
    participant Main
    participant DFS as DFS Approach
    participant BFS as BFS Approach
    participant Grid as Grid State
    
    Note over Grid: Example Grid:<br/>1 1 0<br/>1 0 0<br/>0 0 1

    %% DFS Approach
    rect rgb(200, 230, 200)
    Note over Main,Grid: DFS Approach
    Main->>+DFS: findIslands()
    Note over DFS: Island count = 0
    
    DFS->>Grid: Visit (0,0)
    Note over Grid: Mark (0,0)<br/>Recursively visit:<br/>→(0,1)<br/>→(1,0)
    
    DFS->>Grid: Visit (0,1)
    Note over Grid: Mark (0,1)
    
    DFS->>Grid: Visit (1,0)
    Note over Grid: Mark (1,0)
    Note over DFS: First island<br/>fully explored
    
    DFS->>Grid: Visit (2,2)
    Note over Grid: Mark (2,2)
    Note over DFS: Second island<br/>found & explored
    
    DFS-->>-Main: Return 2 islands
    end

    %% BFS Approach
    rect rgb(230, 200, 200)
    Note over Main,Grid: BFS Approach
    Main->>+BFS: findIslands()
    Note over BFS: Island count = 0
    
    BFS->>Grid: Visit (0,0)
    Note over Grid: Add neighbors to queue:<br/>(0,1), (1,0)
    
    BFS->>Grid: Visit (0,1)
    Note over Grid: Process from queue
    
    BFS->>Grid: Visit (1,0)
    Note over Grid: Process from queue<br/>First island complete
    
    BFS->>Grid: Visit (2,2)
    Note over Grid: No neighbors to add<br/>Second island complete
    
    BFS-->>-Main: Return 2 islands
    end

